    <article class="richtext-content " >
        <h2 style="text-align: center;">The CT Paid Leave Podcast</h2>
<p>The United States is the only industrialized nation in the world without a national paid leave policy, and Connecticut is one of only 11 states and the District of Columbia to have a state paid family and medical leave program in place.&nbsp;<br />
<br />
In the Paid Leave Podcast, host Nancy Barrow delves into CT Paid Leave - how it started, how it works, and who it helps. You'll hear from elected officials, individuals who have experienced the life events for which CT Paid Leave was designed, and experts in various fields including healthcare, domestic violence, military affairs, and much more.&nbsp;</p>
